<br>
Here are my tips to actually getting through the recruitment process!<br>
<br>
1- send an email to tempestade@keldar.com to formal apply to the guild. She'll respond with a nice letter that tells a lot about the guild and explains the process.<br>
<br>
2- write a good post in this forum introducing yourself to the guild (our friends and allies read the public section as well). If you want to see an example of a great into post - read other's (especially if you can findTeograth's :)  )<br>
<br>
When either (or preferably both) are done - I'll create a voting topic in our private voting section. This is where the hard part begins - you need to get 10 votes for membership.<br>
<br>
3- If you have a good friend in the guild - you might considering asking them to sponser you. Consider this carefully because this is a very serious request, and you don't want to put someone "on the spot" and feel bad about rejecting you if they don't fel comfortable about being in that role.<br>
<br>
4- The best thing you can do to get to know DoK members is to go on an event. Click on the Dragons of Kel'dar banner at the top of this screen to go there. Unfortunately if you aren't the level range as the majority of DoK this may not be possible for our "raids" but when we have a guild meeting or other social event (newbie buff day for example) make sure you try to attend those.<br>
<br>
5- Get to know your mentor very well - they can always be reached by name@keldar.com where name is their in-game name. Look for them online and say hi. I would recommend putting them on your /friend list<br>
<br>
6- Do a /who "Dragons of Kel`Dar" all to see up to 20 members online. (note the use of " and `) Feel free to give tells to people in the guild saying hi and tell ttem what you're up to in game. Especially look for people in your level range to group with.<br>
<br>
7- Don't feel bad if it takes a while or you see others get voted on faster than you. If you're patient you'll get through it - and it should work out fine.<br>
<br>
8- If you start another character - or play on multiples - make sure you let your mentor know that and we'll keep that information on our recruiting status page; if you're not on as the character you applied on - we may not find you.<br>
<br>
Good luck - and feel free to contact me directly (slyde@keldar.com) if you have any more questions - and don't forget to stay in contact with your mentor! <br>
